=head1 DESCRIPTION

The details and metrics for the given recommendation.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 AccountId => Str

The AccountID that the recommendation is generated for.


=head2 AccountScope => Str

The account scope that you want your recommendations for. Amazon Web
Services calculates recommendations including the management account
and member accounts if the value is set to PAYER. If the value is
LINKED, recommendations are calculated for individual member accounts
only.


=head2 CurrencyCode => Str

The currency code that Amazon Web Services used to generate the
recommendation and present potential savings.


=head2 CurrentAverageCoverage => Str

The average value of hourly coverage over the lookback period.


=head2 CurrentAverageHourlyOnDemandSpend => Str

The average value of hourly On-Demand spend over the lookback period of
the applicable usage type.


=head2 CurrentMaximumHourlyOnDemandSpend => Str

The highest value of hourly On-Demand spend over the lookback period of
the applicable usage type.


=head2 CurrentMinimumHourlyOnDemandSpend => Str

The lowest value of hourly On-Demand spend over the lookback period of
the applicable usage type.


=head2 EstimatedAverageCoverage => Str

The estimated coverage of the recommended Savings Plan.


=head2 EstimatedAverageUtilization => Str

The estimated utilization of the recommended Savings Plan.


=head2 EstimatedMonthlySavingsAmount => Str

The estimated monthly savings amount based on the recommended Savings
Plan.


=head2 EstimatedOnDemandCost => Str

The remaining On-Demand cost estimated to not be covered by the
recommended Savings Plan, over the length of the lookback period.


=head2 EstimatedOnDemandCostWithCurrentCommitment => Str

The estimated On-Demand costs you expect with no additional commitment,
based on your usage of the selected time period and the Savings Plan
you own.


=head2 EstimatedROI => Str

The estimated return on investment that's based on the recommended
Savings Plan that you purchased. This is calculated as
estimatedSavingsAmount/estimatedSPCost*100.


=head2 EstimatedSavingsAmount => Str

The estimated savings amount that's based on the recommended Savings
Plan over the length of the lookback period.


=head2 EstimatedSavingsPercentage => Str

The estimated savings percentage relative to the total cost of
applicable On-Demand usage over the lookback period.


=head2 EstimatedSPCost => Str

The cost of the recommended Savings Plan over the length of the
lookback period.


=head2 ExistingHourlyCommitment => Str

The existing hourly commitment for the Savings Plan type.


=head2 GenerationTimestamp => Str




=head2 HourlyCommitmentToPurchase => Str

The recommended hourly commitment level for the Savings Plan type and
the configuration that's based on the usage during the lookback period.


=head2 InstanceFamily => Str

The instance family of the recommended Savings Plan.


=head2 LatestUsageTimestamp => Str




=head2 LookbackPeriodInDays => Str

How many days of previous usage that Amazon Web Services considers when
making this recommendation.


=head2 MetricsOverLookbackPeriod => ArrayRef[L<Paws::CostExplorer::RecommendationDetailHourlyMetrics>]

The related hourly cost, coverage, and utilization metrics over the
lookback period.


=head2 OfferingId => Str

The unique ID that's used to distinguish Savings Plans from one
another.


=head2 PaymentOption => Str

The payment option for the commitment (for example, All Upfront or No
Upfront).


=head2 Region => Str

The region the recommendation is generated for.


=head2 SavingsPlansType => Str

The requested Savings Plan recommendation type.


=head2 TermInYears => Str

The term of the commitment in years.


=head2 UpfrontCost => Str

The upfront cost of the recommended Savings Plan, based on the selected
payment option.



